000502_9934bcc2-334b-d52a-0cb9-5e956ecc2ec0 Hanging paragraph in clause
<clause id="_9934bcc2-334b-d52a-0cb9-5e956ecc2ec0" obligation="normative">
<title id="_ffde8941-2fb5-3b81-42b0-6f720cc7d76a">Hazard identification</title>
<p id="_896cd989-f478-4450-1602-7c212d1a559f">The substance poses high potential risks for human health if handled inappropriately. It is acutely toxic by inhalation, in contact with skin and if swallowed. Exposure to ZEN solutions may cause reproductive disorders, skin or eye corrosion, cough, shortness of breath, headache, nausea and vomiting. Recommendations for handling high-purity solid samples of ZEN are given in reference <eref type="inline" bibitemid="westwood" citeas="[4]"/>.</p>

<p id="_a816b01a-0e92-24d8-60c4-53e8cbf280b5"> <strong>DISCLAIMER:</strong> The safety recommendations given in this section are based on best practice reported in the literature and are not verified by the BIPM.</p>

000728methods Hanging paragraph in clause
<clause id="_5d30912b-03e2-5d30-7605-97b48db7dbcb" anchor="methods" obligation="normative">
<title id="_c77e8a97-8d8d-85ad-26b3-53f187e881e4">Methods for the characterization of zearalenone solutions</title>
<p id="_88e95548-d136-2cc6-7106-622b4f297f88">This section of the Guideline describes the methods developed during the BIPM MMCBKT programme for the characterization of ZEN stock and calibration solutions prepared from the source ZEN material. The methods are the basis for the stability and homogeneity studies and for the analytical confirmation of the ZEN mass fraction value assigned gravimetrically.</p>

<p id="_9f1cbca6-2610-e181-41fc-1011ef0049f3"> <strong>DISCLAIMER:</strong> Commercial instruments, software and materials are identified in this document in order to describe some procedures. This does not imply a recommendation or endorsement by the BIPM nor does it imply that any of the instruments, equipment and materials identified are necessarily the best available for the purpose.</p>

000734_8d565e58-2635-c5f3-37d4-30443bfcc1d9 Hanging paragraph in clause
<clause id="_8d565e58-2635-c5f3-37d4-30443bfcc1d9" obligation="normative">
<title id="_99480420-e9bf-42f8-63a6-af16bd7f88e1">ZEN and related structure impurities analysis by LC-DAD-MS/MS</title>
<p id="_fc0a498a-e6dd-c530-8eac-4717a2fbb66d">A method based on liquid chromatography inline coupled to diode array detection (DAD) and tandem mass spectrometry (MS/MS) was developed for the quantification of related structure impurities in the ZEN source material (BIPM ref. OGO.178). Details on the method development and validation are described in the purity evaluation guideline. <eref type="inline" bibitemid="westwood" citeas="[4]"/> Briefly, commercial standards were purchased for the potential impurities ZAN, a-ZEL, b-ZEL, a-ZAL and b-ZAL (<xref target="fig2"/>). The purity of ZAN was assessed by qNMR while for the rest of impurities it was taken from information in the supplier’s certificates. ZEN (BIPM ref. OGO.178) and ZAN (BIPM ref. OGO.182) materials obtained from <em>Chemtek., Inc. First Standard</em> were used to prepare <asciimath>200 "unitsml(mg/kg)"</asciimath> acetonitrile solutions that served as the basis for the LC method development. The impurity standards were used to optimize the chromatographic separation and MS/MS detection parameters that are reported below. The method was validated in-house for the performance characteristics of linearity, precision and limits of detection and quantification.</p>
